(Overview) Tj
T*
(Parts of speech classify words by their roles in sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Explain the meaning of Parts of Speech in English using accurate subject vocabulary.) Tj
T*
(- Describe the key ideas behind nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, and other word) Tj
T*
(classes.) Tj
T*
(- Apply Parts of Speech to examples such as identifying the function of a word within a) Tj
T*
(sentence.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid common errors and build confidence through sentence analysis by word class.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Parts of speech classify words by their roles in sentences. In a textbook lesson, the) Tj
T*
(first goal is to make the language idea clear. Students should be able to explain what) Tj
T*
(Parts of Speech means, identify where it appears in English, and describe the main) Tj
T*
(purpose of the topic without relying on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Parts of Speech is nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, and other) Tj
T*
(word classes. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the) Tj
T*
(idea actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or) Tj
T*
(patterns behind Parts of Speech and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In) Tj
T*
(English, success usually depends on understanding the meaning, form, and effect that) Tj
T*
(belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Parts of Speech is to connect the explanation directly to) Tj
T*
(identifying the function of a word within a sentence. That kind of language example) Tj
T*
(shows students how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner) Tj
T*
(should be able to state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the) Tj
T*
(question, and then apply the interpretation or writing method with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
(One common difficulty in Parts of Speech is classifying a word without checking how it) Tj
T*
(is used. This matters because many learners can repeat a definition but still fail to) Tj
T*
