T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect sentence analysis by word class. The most effective habit is to read) Tj
T*
(the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a similar) Tj
T*
(question alone. This turns Parts of Speech into something the student can genuinely) Tj
T*
(study and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Parts of Speech should first be understood as a language idea before it is treated as) Tj
T*
(an exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, and other word classes) Tj
T*
(because it controls how questions in Parts of Speech are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Parts of Speech uses the correct interpretation or writing method) Tj
T*
(and explains why that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Identifying the function of a word within a sentence is the type of application that) Tj
T*
(helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Parts of Speech.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind nouns, verbs, adjectives,) Tj
T*
(adverbs, and other word classes.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct interpretation or writing method step by step instead of jumping to) Tj
T*
(the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on identifying the function of a word within a sentence.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, and other word classes) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Parts of Speech step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on sentence analysis by word class.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid classifying a word without checking how it is used while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
